<seg id="540">Opening Envelopes</seg>
<seg id="541">Opening Envelopes</seg>
<seg id="542">During the opening of the envelopes, tenders that have been closed are opened, their contents are read and published.</seg>
<seg id="543">The period during which a tenderer is bound by his tender shall begin at the time of expiry of the time-limit for submitting the envelopes or opening them and shall end at a time-limit specified by the contracting authority.</seg>
<seg id="544">European law requirements and prevention of corruption</seg>
<seg id="545">European legislation does not contain any specific provisions on the opening of envelopes.</seg>
<seg id="546">However, national laws and regulations contain extensive requirements to protect bids and competitors during this sensitive phase of the entire procurement procedure.</seg>
