<seg id="594">Assessment and evaluation of tenders</seg>
<seg id="595">The contracting authority must examine and evaluate the tenders received within the time limit set.</seg>
<seg id="596">At the same time, it must award the contract to the tenderer which best meets the award criteria in the tender.</seg>
<seg id="597">European law requirements and prevention of corruption</seg>
<seg id="598">EU law provides for a process of evaluation and evaluation of tenders in several steps:</seg>
<seg id="599">The first step is to check candidates' suitability.</seg>
<seg id="600">They must be in a good economic and financial position and possess the required professional and technical knowledge and skills.</seg>
<seg id="601">Candidates who have ever been convicted of bribery or defrauding by a final judgment must always be excluded from procurement procedures.</seg>
