<seg id="849">According to the wording of Act No. 235/2004 Coll., effective from 1 January 2005, in the case of the supply of electricity, the place of performance is the place where the customer has his registered office, place of business or where he has an establishment for which the goods are supplied.</seg>
<seg id="850">Therefore, Czech payers should not have reported the supply of electricity to SH in 2005.</seg>
<seg id="851">By reporting the intra-community supply of electricity in SH, both above-mentioned payers distorted the VIES data by a total of CZK 503,881,939 (EUR 16,917,873).</seg>
<seg id="852">Conclusion</seg>
<seg id="853">The cooperation fulfilled the goals of the Czech National Bank and the SAO.</seg>
<seg id="854">Both SAIs gained a deeper knowledge of VAT management systems in the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="855">The cooperation revealed differences between the two systems and showed that the VAT administration legislation differs.</seg>
<seg id="856">Suspicious cases of intra-community transactions were identified during the parallel controls.</seg>
<seg id="857">Some of them are worth checking out afterwards.</seg>
<seg id="858">On the basis of the audit findings, both SAIs made recommendations concerning the administration of VAT.</seg>
<seg id="859">The follow-up of these recommendations should also be part of the follow-up.</seg>
<seg id="860">The new experience and knowledge gained through the cooperation between the two audit institutions is the basis for the successful implementation of the following VAT management checks.</seg>
<seg id="861">Communiqué</seg>
<seg id="862">The report was drawn up in Czech, English and German and signed by the President of the Supreme Audit Office, Czech Republic and the President of the Bundesrechnungshof, Federal Republic of Germany.</seg>
</p>
